Privacy Policy

Photo to PDF Converter - PDFio

Last Updated: February 9, 2026

Introduction

This Privacy Policy describes how Photo to PDF Converter - PDFio ("we," "our," or "the App") handles your information. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our data practices.

Information We Collect

Photos and Files
The App accesses your photos, camera, and files solely to convert images into PDF documents. All image processing occurs locally on your device. We do not upload, store, or transmit your photos, files, or generated PDFs to any external server.

Camera Access
The App requests camera access to allow you to scan documents. Camera data is processed entirely on your device and is never transmitted externally.

Subscription Information
If you subscribe to PDFio Pro, your purchase is processed by Apple through the App Store. We use RevenueCat to manage subscription status. RevenueCat receives an anonymous app user ID to verify your entitlement. We do not collect your name, email, or payment details through this process.

Locally Stored Data
The App stores the following data locally on your device using standard device storage:

Your generated PDF documents
App preferences and settings
Daily usage counters (e.g., share count) for free-tier limit tracking
This data remains on your device and is not transmitted to us or any third party.

Information We Do Not Collect

We do not collect, store, or share:

Personal identification information (name, email, phone number)
Location data
Browsing history or analytics
Device identifiers for advertising
Any user-generated content (photos, documents, PDFs)
Third-Party Services

RevenueCat
We use RevenueCat to manage in-app subscriptions. RevenueCat processes anonymous transaction data provided by Apple. You can review RevenueCat's privacy policy at https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy.

Apple App Store
All purchases are processed through Apple's App Store. Apple's privacy policy governs how your payment information is handled.

Data Security

Since all your data (photos, PDFs, and documents) is processed and stored locally on your device, it is protected by your device's built-in security features, including device passcode, Face ID, or Touch ID.

Children's Privacy

The App does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13. Since we do not collect personal data from any users, the App is safe for use by all ages.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected by an updated "Last Updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.

Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

https://app.supp05.com
